TY  - JOUR
AU  - Müller, D
TI  - Use of cooperative game theory as a tool for the control of cooperations - an analysis
T2  - BETRIEBSWIRTSCHAFTLICHE FORSCHUNG UND PRAXIS
AB  - Several methods and instruments are used to support management and control of firm's cooperation. These instruments have to meet both requirements, which are placed on decision models as demands which are made on incentive models. Solution concepts of cooperative game theory have received scarce attention in this context. Therefore, the paper presents basic characteristics of cooperative game theory and three solution concepts in detail. Moreover, the question arises, why cooperative game theory plays a minor role. It will be shown, that this subdomain of game theory may provide an efficient and consistent way of fulfilling the combined incentive-decision-model requirements. Main reasons for the unimportance of cooperative game solutions are the special way of modelling and some of the necessary assumptions.
