AB  - We provide, in minimum cost spanning tree problems, a general framework to identify the family of rules satisfying monotonicity over cost and population. We also prove that the set of allocations induced by the family coincides with the so-called irreducible core, that results from decreasing the cost of the arcs as much as possible, without reducing the minimal cost.
