TI  - Condition optimizing, process predicting, and key physicochemical factor identifying for yak dung compost humification: Integrating response surface methodology with interpretable machine learning
T2  - CHEMICAL ENGINEERING JOURNAL
AB  - Enhancing the humification of yak dung compost is critical for advancing resource recycling and ecological conservation on the Qinghai-Xizang Plateau. However, practical implementation faces three technical and theoretical bottlenecks: ambiguous operational conditions, cumbersome indicator measurement procedures, and unidentified key physicochemical factors. To address these challenges, we developed a novel integrative framework synergizing response surface methodology (RSM) with interpretable machine learning (ML). A threefactor RSM experiment (carbon/nitrogen [C/N] ratio: 25-35; aeration rate: 0.2-0.8 L/min/kg; moisture content: 60 %-70 %) was designed to quantify the influence of operating conditions on the humification index (HI) of the final organic fertilizer and determine the optimal conditions. Physicochemical factors and HI were simultaneously monitored at different composting stages. Seven ML models were developed to predict HI outcomes during composting, with the Shapley additive explanations (SHAP) algorithm applied to identify key driving factors. RSM results demonstrated that HI was predominantly governed by the C/N ratio (negative correlation), followed by aeration rate (positive correlation). The condition combination maximizing HI was identified as C/N = 25.1, aeration rate = 0.77 L/min/kg, with moisture content without requiring precise control. Gradient Boosting Regression Trees achieved exceptional predictive accuracy for HI dynamics (R2 = 0.93, RMSE = 1.86, MAE = 1.43, AIC = 96.0). Total organic carbon content was the most critical predictor of HI by SHAP algorithm. Composting technology aimed at increasing organic matter decomposition efficiency can further improve humification. The research results provide technical support and theoretical basis for the accurate and intelligent development of yak manure composting technology.
